        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 8:42PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 841 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Drayton, or 9 miles
west of Vienna, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Vienna, Unadilla, Pinehurst, Lilly, Drayton, Richwood, Flint River
Wma, and Tremont.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
